 article will walk you through the steps to create new products at the manage products screen youll learn how to add products associate locations add colors and much more by default there are three products already set up in your site mat rental towel rental and water note your manage products features will vary based on your subscription level  content add product required fields basic information sell online color  size inventory membership restrictions  discounts  product commissions additional information  add product click the home tab select products from the submenu click the add new button   this opens the add a new product form under the basic information section you can begin entering the required product details like the product’s name and price below the basic information section you’ll find additional sections where you can add more details about each product or add multiple product variants at once note these fields are optional required fields marked by asterisks after you have enter a product name and price in the basic information section  you have the option to skip to the bottom ignoring all the other fields in this screen and clicking on one of the add buttons    if you click the add button you’ll go right back to the manage products screen where you can search to see your new product if you click the save  add next button a new add a product form will open and you can continue adding products back to top   basic information product name required enter the product’s name if you are adding a group of products this name will apply to all color and size combinations which we call variants that you add  product price required enter the price that clients will pay for this product  sales tax if you have tax rates enabled you’ll see all of them here make sure to check only the rates that you want to apply when clients purchase this product wholesale cost type in the amount of money the supplier charged you for this product your markup percentage will display to the right of the product price barcode enter a barcode manually or click your cursor in the field and scan the product’s barcode you can also leave the barcode field blank to let mindbody generate one for you if you use variable barcodes check the “use variable pricing” box and enter only the fivedigit product id portion of the barcode into the field you can search for retail products by barcode or even use them to take physical inventory with our inventory tickets feature sold at locations leave this set at “all locations” or choose the specific locations where this product will be sold category choose the main revenue category for this product if you don’t see one that fits choose  add a new category and enter a new category name if you do not make a selection sales of this product will show up under the “unassigned” category in reports note you can use the category to organize your online store  subcategory  add a subcategory to give more definition to your products for example men’s women’s or kids’ could be subcategories within your clothing category  second category second categories aren’t dependent on the main category they just add another searchable label to a product for example if you have a workout mat that’s made of recycled material you could put it in the equipment category and add green products as the second category sales and holiday are other common second categories you can enable second categories on the general setup  options screen   back to top   sell online sell online check the box to allow clients to purchase this product in consumer mode online price by default the online sale price will match the instore price if you want to set a different online price click this link and then change the price in the field if you create a single product ie a product that comes only in one size and color this image will be linked to it automatically clients will see the image when they browse your products in the online store and when they select the item for purchase if you add more than one size or color option at once ie you create multiple variants the image will be added to the first color and size combo you added—also known as the default product variant this means that clients will see the image when they browse products in the online store however it won’t appear if clients select the item and then look at a variant other than the default  note if you want to add images to each product variant or choose a new default product variant you can just add the product group and then find and edit the individual items image   image hover text select choose image to upload clients will see this text when they hover over a product image after they click the products tab in your online store enter a maximum of eighty characters online product description this is a longer more detailed description that clients will see after they click on a product picture enter it into the text editor and then format it using the tools at the top or click the html button and use approved html tags  shipping weight enter the item’s shipping weight the minimum is  pounds or kilograms online store inventory location choose the location that will ship the item to the client if you do not make a choice the system will default to the “ecommerce order fulfillment location” set in your general setup  options screen check the box to update inventory location for all colors and sizes click here to learn more about shipping products sold in your online store back to top color and size  color choose the color or colors that this product comes in if the right color isn’t available in the list click  add a new color and create it you could even use this field to record scents flavors fabrics etc size choose the size or sizes that this product comes in if the right size isn’t available in the list click  add a new size and create it remember size isn’t limited to small medium and large you could even use this field to record product weights in pounds or kilograms bottle sizes in ounces or milligrams etc  important notes as you add colors and sizes the system creates one product variant for every possible size and color combination if you end up with any variants that you don’t actually carry maybe your blue shirts come in large and medium but yellow shirts are available only in medium you can discontinue them on the manage products screen when you add a group of products the same price will apply to all size and color variants you add you can edit this from manage products after the product name applies to all size and color variants so if one variant must have its own name—fundraiser tshirt instead of logo tshirt for example—you should add it as a separate item instead of a variant  back to top inventory number in stock enter the number of units for sale at each location if you added more than one color or size you’ll need to add the number in stock later it’s easiest to do this from the inventory on hand report but you can also edit an individual variant and enter the number in stock there manufacturer id enter the number given to the product by its manufacturer you can adjust your retail settings on the general setup  options screen so that the manufacturer id prints on sales receipts barcode label text by default the barcode label will print the product name above the product color and size to change this click the “edit” link to the right of either line and enter new text you can also quickly print a barcode from this page by clicking print barcode note the ability to print barcode will appear after the product has been added purchase order options these fields help you generate purchase orders automatically select the item’s supplier and then fill in the maximum inventory level reorder level and lot size note lot size is the minimum number of units that can be ordered from the supplier your orders will always be a multiple of the lot size click here to learn more about adjusting inventory in your site back to top membership restrictions  discounts restrict who can purchase this product  if anyone can buy it leave this set at “no” if only those clients with certain memberships can buy it select “yes” then click into the field to the right of “who can purchase this” and check the boxes next to any applicable memberships  please note that if you restricted the purchase of this product to specific memberships only those memberships will show up in this list do any member discounts apply to this product if membership discounts do not apply leave this set at “no” if certain membership discounts apply select “yes” then click into the field to the right of “who gets discounts on this” and check the boxes next to any applicable memberships  click here to learn more about setting up memberships in your site back to top product commissions do staff members receive standard commission for this product choose “yes” if staff should receive commission for this product you must also enter a standard commission rate on the staff member’s staffhourlypay rates screen if you want staff to earn the standard commission rate listed on the staffhourlypay rates screen leave this one set at  if you want staff to earn additional commission for this product on top of the standard rate or if the standard rate is set at  but you want staff to earn money for this sale then enter that additional percentage rate or flat amount here  choose “no” if staff do not receive commission for this product do staff members receive promotional commission for this product  choose “yes” if staff should receive commission for this product you must also enter a promotional commission rate on the staff member’s staffhourlypay rates screen if you want staff to earn that promotional commission rate leave this one set at  if you want staff to earn additional commission for this product on top of the promotional rate or if the promotional rate is set at  but you want staff to earn money for this sale then enter that additional percentage rate or flat amount here  choose “no” if staff do not receive commission for this product note if you choose to enter an amount in all commission rates then you are indicating to the the system that the staff member will receive  different commissions for that one product back to top   additional information   product notes enter notes about this product these are internal notes that will display only when you or your staff look up the product from the retail screen  product type  this is a costume check the box if you want to be able to rent or sell this product to clients when they check out of a class or an enrollment  click here to learn more about costumes and costume tracking this is a professional product check the box if you want to sell this item to your staff members only when staff members buy professional products the purchase price is deducted from their pay because of this professional products cannot be sold online and products that are sold online cannot be marked as professional products if you want to make the same product available to your clients create two separate items one that is a professional product and one that isn’t quick cash product  quick cash products are items that you can sell quickly without having to navigate away from your class signin screen while you are enrolling clients click here to learn more note if you would like to use the quick cash option the product must be added first favorite products use this feature if you sell certain items more often than others and you want them to show up in a condensed favorite products menu on your retail screen click here to learn more you’ll be able to skip the search and click just once to select it note if you would like to use the favorite products option the product must be added first back to top additional resources shipping using html throughout your site logging and adjusting inventory auto generated purchase orders commissions costume tracking favo